cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses device-to-device (D2D) communication, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of different waveforms (OFDM and FBMC/OQAM) for D2D communication and compares their performance, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper discusses the coexistence of OFDM and FBMC/OQAM for underlay D2D communication in 5G networks, which is a topic related to communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the system-level performance of a set-up for D2D communication, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of different waveforms for D2D communication and their impact on inter-D2D interference, which is related to multimedia.
